
    JavaScript Need to Know:

    JavaScript Array Operators:

1) arr.filter(function(item)) - returns an array of matching values
2) arr.Maps(function(item)) - contructs a new array
3) arr.Find(function(item)) - get only the first matching element
4) arr.forEach(function(item)) - loop thru an array
5) arr.some.(function(item))  - some elements in array has a condition
6) arr.every.(function(item)) - every element in array has a condition
7) arr.reduce.(function(firstElement, EveryNextElement)) - An Operator on array elements
8) arr.Includes(string)
9) arr1.concat(arr2) - joint 2 are more arrays into one
10) arr.Join - turn two are more arrays into a string
11) Array.from(string) - creates an array from a string
12) arr.slice(int indexStartLeft, int indexStartRight) - select elements from an array
13) arr.shift() - Permanently Removes first element of array, returns value of removed element
14) arr.splice(int startIndex, int AmountTobeRemoved, string, string) - Permanently add/remove array elements
15) arr.unshift(string, string ) - add elements to front of array
16) arr.sort(), arr.reverse()
17) arr.keys() - return an array of keys
18) arr.findIndex(function(item)), arr.indexOf('word') - get the index of an item that meets condition


    JavaScript Strings

1) str.replace('string', 'replace')
2) str.substr(int startIndex, int LastIndex)
3) str.search(string) - search for a value within an array and returns it location
4) str.split("char")
5) str.match(/regex/gi) - for regex
6) str.concat(str2)
7) str.includes('word')
8) str.slice(int startIndex, int LastIndex)
9) str.toLowerCase()


loops:

for( let char in array) - for-in returns the index.
for ( let char of array ) - for-of returns the value.
